                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.6363 ST 2/199: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-30T10:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 30, 1937—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 30—9:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. Referring to my telegram No. 65, November 16, 9 a.m., in extended
                    conversation with new Foreign Minister yesterday I asked: <pb facs="0318"
                        n="308" xml:id="pg_308"/>
                    <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>whether Government was ready to undertake direct conversations;</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>to extend 90-day period sufficiently to allow adequate preparation of
                            case for courts; or (3) to suggest an alternative solution of Standard
                            Oil Company problem.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>The Foreign Minister replied he was not familiar with recent developments but
                    would present my inquiries to Junta in a friendly spirit and hoping for a prompt
                    and constructive reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
